At this page you can exercise your legal privacy rights, including requesting a copy of the identifiable data we hold about you, having data deleted, opting out of having sensitive data used (which we will treat as a data deletion request), and opting out of having your data sold or shared for marketing purposes.  In some countries you may have other rights, like the right to object to or to limit processing.  For these, please select "Delete My Data."  We also provide you the ability to opt out of receiving offers by email from us.  Please select from the options below (you may choose more than one).
We organize our databases around email addresses, so you must submit a separate request for each email address you use. Our automated process will then verify that you are the authorized user of that email account.
If you would like more information about how Zeta uses personal information, please read our privacy policies
here
. If you would like to see data that is linked to your devices and used for online advertising, but that does not identify you directly, click
here
. If you are a Zeta employee or applicant, please contact your Zeta HR representative to request a copy of your HR-related data.
Requests may take up to 45 days to process. Requests made from Canada or the EEA will be processed within 30 days. If we are processing a high volume of requests we may advise you that a request could take up to 90 days to process, as allowed by applicable laws.
